Gabriela is responsible for technical projects at The Tor Project.She coordinates roadmaps, tracks priorities, and ensures that Tor is always thinking “user first.” She has been developing software for over 20 years working for companies and nonprofits in Uruguay, California, and internationally. Prior of joining Tor, Gabriela coordinated a program on gender and technology at Tactical Tech Collective in Latin America. Before she worked as a software engineer at the Mozilla Foundation, developing tools for journalists and newsrooms at the Coral project. 
